article.headline: Wildcats win tourney championship
article.linkText: Mahoney hits triple-double in No. 13 Kansas State win
article.story:
MANHATTAN, Kan. (AP) -- Megan Mahoney had 12 points, 12 assists,
and 10 rebounds, and Kendra Wecker added 18 points to lead No. 13
Kansas State past Saint Louis 94-54 Saturday in the championship
game of the Wildcat Classic.

Mahoney scored all her points in the second half to become the
second Kansas State player to have a triple-double.

Kansas State (5-2) shot 64 percent from the floor in the first
half and put the game out of reach early. The Wildcats cruised in
the second half to win their 12th in the tournament they hold.

Laurie Koehn added 17 points for Kansas State, Nicole Ohlde
scored 13 and Claire Coggins had 11.

Lakrisha Brown led Saint Louis (5-2) with 15 points. Angie Lewis
added 14.

Kansas State made six of its first seven shots, but Lewis scored
six straight during an 8-2 run that cut the lead to four.

Koehn then hit a jumper in the lane with 12:53 to go in the half
to start a 13-4 run that put Kansas State up for good.
